          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped mint</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and <strong>grated cucumber</strong> in a small bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>tzatziki</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced cucumber</strong>, <strong>tomato</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped mint</strong> to the pot with the <strong>drained bulgur wheat</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and squeeze in the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s]</strong>, season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tabbouleh</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>wholemeal pitta[s]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 2-3 min or until warmed through</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1576.-step-7-x400.jpg",
